# HeroUI v3 (this monorepo)

Stack: **HeroUI v3** (`@heroui/react` + `@heroui/styles`), **Tailwind CSS v4**, **React Aria** under the hood.

## Do / don’t

- **No `HeroUIProvider`** — v3 does not require an app-wide HeroUI provider.
- Prefer **compound components** (`Card.Header`, `Modal.Dialog`, `Select.Trigger` + `Select.Popover` + `ListBox`, etc.). Avoid v2 flat APIs (`ModalContent`, `CardBody`, `SelectItem`, …).
- Prefer **`onPress`** on interactive HeroUI controls; use **`variant`** on `Button` — not legacy `color` / `variant="bordered"` / `variant="light"` unless mapped to v3 (`outline`, `ghost`, …).
- **Styling:** `@import "tailwindcss"` then `@import "@heroui/styles"` in app `index.css`; add `@source` for `node_modules/@heroui/react` and `@heroui/styles` so Tailwind sees component classes. Do not use `@heroui/theme` or the old `heroui({ themes })` Tailwind plugin.
- **Forms:** `Input` has no `label` prop — pair **`Label`** (from `@heroui/react`) with `Input` / `TextArea` / selects.
- **Tables:** use `Table` → `Table.ScrollContainer` → `Table.Content` → header/body; no `removeWrapper` / `emptyContent` — handle empty UI in the route.

## Docs

For props and examples, use the repo skill **heroui-react** (`.agents/skills/heroui-react/SKILL.md`) and its scripts, or HeroUI’s official v3 docs — **ignore v2-only patterns** (provider, `@heroui/theme`, `classNames` slots where v3 uses composition + `className`).
